---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Louisville Anti-Displacement Assessment Tool (ADAT) | Housing Policy Resource"
  description="Learn about Louisville's Anti-Displacement Assessment Tool (ADAT) - a free public platform to assess housing development impact on communities and prevent displacement."
>
  <main class="main-container">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section
      class="hero-section"
      style="background-image: url('/assets/education/skyhouse.jpg')"
    >
      <div class="hero-content">
        <!-- Header -->
        <header class="header">
          <div class="header-content">
            <nav class="header-nav">
              <div class="header-left">
                <img src="/assets/education/ADT master file_img/source/image.png" alt="Louisville Metro Logo" class="logo" />
                <div class="nav-links">
                  <a href="/assessment" class="nav-link">
                    <span class="nav-text">Assessment</span>
                  </a>
                  <a href="/resources" class="nav-link">
                    <span class="nav-text">Resources</span>
                  </a>
                </div>
              </div>
            </nav>
          </div>
        </header>

        <!-- Hero Content -->
        <div class="hero-text-section">
          <h1 class="hero-title">What is Displacement?</h1>
          <div class="hero-description">
            <img src="/assets/education/ADT master file_icon/Vector (Stroke).svg" alt="Displacement icon" class="hero-icon" />
            <p class="hero-desc-text">
              Displacement is when people are forced to leave their homes due to rising costs, gentrification, or urban development.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ADAT Section -->
    <section class="content-section">
      <div class="scroll-container">
        <div class="section-content">
          <div class="section-header">
            <div class="section-icon-container">
              <img src="/assets/education/ADT master file_icon/Union.svg" alt="ADAT icon" class="section-icon" />
            </div>
            <h2 class="section-title">What is the Anti-Displacement Assessment Tool (ADAT)?</h2>
          </div>

          <div class="divider-line"></div>

          <div class="scroll-indicator">
            <div class="scroll-text-container">
              <span class="scroll-text">Scroll</span>
              <img src="/assets/education/ADT master file_icon/Chevron down.svg" alt="Scroll indicator" class="scroll-icon" />
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="main-content">
            <div class="content-row">
              <div class="content-left">
                <div class="text-content-container">
                  <p class="main-text">
                    The Anti-Displacement Assessment Tool (ADAT) was created in response to the
                    <span class="text-bold text-underline"> Anti-Displacement Ordinance</span> passed by Louisville Metro City Council on November 9th, 2023.
                    <span class="text-bold"> This law requires that new housing projects receiving city support, such as tax breaks or official letters of support, be reviewed for their potential to displace current residents.</span>
                    <br /><br />
                    The ADAT is a public and free-to-use platform that helps assess how new housing developments may affect local communities.
                    <span class="text-bold"> Its purpose is to prevent displacement and to support fair, equitable, and inclusive neighborhood growth.</span>
                    <br /><br />
                    Developed by researchers at Boston University and the University of Southern California in collaboration with Metro Louisville, the ADAT determines the risk of displacement associated with the location of projects seeking Metro support and the required affordability level required for the project to mitigate displacement.
                  </p>

                  <!-- MHC video (555 × 305) -->
                  <div class="video-wrapper">
                    <video
                      class="right-video"
                      src="/assets/education/mhc.mp4"
                      controls
                      playsinline
                      preload="metadata"
                      poster="/assets/education/architect.png"
                    >
                      Your browser does not support the video tag.
                    </video>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <p class="image-caption">
                  Learn more about Area Median Income (AMI) from the <span class="text-underline">Metropolitan Housing Coalition</span>
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="content-right">
                <div class="right-content-top">
                  <!-- News video (555 × 305) -->
                  <div class="video-wrapper">
                    <video
                      class="right-video"
                      src="/assets/education/news.mp4"
                      controls
                      playsinline
                      preload="metadata"
                      poster="/assets/education/architect.png"
                    >
                      Your browser does not support the video tag.
                    </video>
                  </div>

                  <p class="right-caption">
                    Learn more about Louisville's <span class="text-underline">Anti-displacement Ordinance</span>
                  </p>
                </div>

                <div class="right-content-bottom">
                  <h3 class="right-subtitle">How does the ADAT work?</h3>
                  <p class="right-text">
                    The tool uses Area Median Income (AMI) to understand what is considered 'affordable', in a given neighborhood. AMI is updated every year by the
                    U.S. Department of Housing and Urban Development (HUD), and it depends on where you live and how many people are in your household. This tool
                    uses the AMI for a typical household of 3 to 4 people in the Louisville area.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Louisville Housing Need Section -->
    <section class="content-section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-icon-container">
          <img src="/assets/education/ADT master file_icon/Vector-3.svg" alt="Housing need icon" class="section-icon" />
        </div>
        <h2 class="section-title">Louisville Housing Need</h2>
      </div>

      <!-- Overview Section -->
      <div class="overview-content">
        <div class="divider-line"></div>
        <h3 class="overview-title">Overview</h3>

        <p class="overview-text">
          Louisville Metro produced a comprehensive
          <a href="https://louisvilleky.gov/housing-needs-assessment" class="u" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Housing Needs Assessment</a>
          in 2019 that was updated in 2024. The assessment identified
          <span class="strong"> two critical factors</span>
          that contribute to displacement risk. First, nearly all people with income below 50% AMI are housing cost burdened and pay more than 30% of their income toward housing (with a substantial share paying more than 50%). Second, there are not enough homes affordable to people with income below 50% of AMI. These two factors are the backbone of this assessment tool.
        </p>

        <div class="rent-burden-section">
          <div class="rent-burden-content">
            <h4 class="rent-burden-title"><strong>Rent Burden</strong></h4>
            <div class="rent-burden-row">
              <p class="rent-burden-quote">
                Louisville is in the midst of a housing crisis, with countless residents struggling to keep up with rising rents
              </p>
              <p class="rent-burden-description">
                Too many families spend over 30% of their income on housing, risking instability and displacement. Louisville urgently needs affordable housing,
                especially for those below 50% AMI. Without action, more residents face housing insecurity or homelessness.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="chart-section">
          <div class="chart-container">
            <img src="/assets/education/ADT master file_img/b4d8f5ad5654373b7be369517f6a1f5 1.png" alt="Rent burden statistics chart" class="chart-image" />
          </div>
          <div class="chart-sidebar">
            <div class="chart-sidebar-container">
              <img src="/assets/education/ADT master file_img/b4d8f5ad5654373b7be369517f6a1f5 1-1.png" alt="Additional housing statistics" class="chart-sidebar-image" />
            </div>
            <a href="#" class="learn-more-btn">Learn more</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Housing Mismatch Section -->
    <section class="housing-mismatch-section">
      <div class="housing-mismatch-content">
        <div class="housing-mismatch-text">
          <h3 class="text-large text-bold">Housing Mismatch</h3>
          <br /><br />
          There are currently a <span class="text-bold text-italic">shortage of affordable housing units for Louisville residents</span>. Currently, there are about
          <span class="text-bold text-italic"> 31,000 units needed</span> for people who make 50% or less of Louisville's AMI.
          <br /><br />
          About half of the most affordable units are rented by households who could afford to pay more. Only one in four households in the lowest income category
          (30% AMI) rents at a level that is affordable to them.
          <br /><br />
          This imbalance makes it challenging for households with the most needs to find affordable housing.
        </div>

        <div class="housing-mismatch-right">
          <div class="housing-chart-container">
            <img src="/assets/education/ADT master file_img/14ec7b8f55e143b30ce00085c17a3c2 2.png" alt="Housing mismatch data visualization" class="housing-chart-image" />
          </div>
          <a href="/housing-data" class="learn-more-btn">Learn more</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Role Section -->
      <section class="content-section">
        <div class="scroll-container">
          <div class="section-content">
            <div class="section-header">
              <div class="section-icon-container">
                <img src="/assets/education/ADT master file_icon/Vector-2.svg" alt="Role icon" class="section-icon" />
              </div>
              <h2 class="section-title">The Role You Play</h2>
            </div>

            <div class="divider-line"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Role Cards Section -->
      <section class="role-cards-section">
        <div class="role-cards-divider">
        </div>

        <div class="role-cards-container">
          <article class="role-card">
            <img src="/assets/education/ADT master file_icon/Ellipse 1-1.svg" alt="City official representative" class="role-card-image" style="width: 48%;" />
            <div class="role-card-content">
              <h3 class="role-card-title">City Officials</h3>
              <p class="role-card-description">Review development proposals using ADAT to ensure projects meet anti-displacement requirements and support equitable growth.</p>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="role-card">
            <img src="/assets/education/ADT master file_icon/Ellipse 2.svg" alt="Community member representative" class="role-card-image" style="width: 36%;" />
            <div class="role-card-content">
              <h3 class="role-card-title">Community Members</h3>
              <p class="role-card-description" style="width: 86%;">Use ADAT to understand how proposed developments may impact your neighborhood and advocate for affordable housing.</p>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="role-card">
            <img src="/assets/education/ADT master file_icon/Ellipse 1.svg" alt="Developer representative" class="role-card-image" style="width: 44%;" />
            <div class="role-card-content">
              <h3 class="role-card-title">Developers</h3>
              <p class="role-card-description">Plan projects that meet affordability requirements and contribute to community stability using ADAT insights.</p>
            </div>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ADAT Usage Section -->
      <section class="content-section">
        <div class="scroll-container">
          <div class="section-content">
            <div class="section-header">
              <div class="section-icon-container">
                <img src="/assets/education/ADT master file_icon/Vector.svg" alt="How to use ADAT icon" class="section-icon" />
              </div>
              <h2 class="section-title">How to Use ADAT</h2>
            </div>

            <div class="divider-line"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="adat-diagram-section">
        <div class="adat-diagram-container">
          <div class="adat-diagram-divider"></div>
          <img src="/assets/education/ADT master file_img/ADATExplainer-DRAFT2 1.png" alt="ADAT tool usage diagram and workflow" class="adat-diagram-image" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <script type="module" src="https://static.rocket.new/rocket-web.js?_cfg=https%3A%2F%2Fdanielsa4079back.builtwithrocket.new&_be=https%3A%2F%2Fapplication.rocket.new&_v=0.1.8" is:inline></script>
<script type="module" src="https://static.rocket.new/rocket-shot.js?v=0.0.1" is:inline></script>
</BaseLayout>
